 A \in \mathbb{R}^{m \times n}, b \in \mathbb{R}^m, c \in \mathbb{R}  
 K:= \{ x \in \mathbb{R}^n: Ax \le b \}
 \iff 
x,y \in K, \lambda \in [0,1]
 \lambda x + (1- \lambda) y
 \in K
m=n=1
Ax\le b
\lambda Ax\le \lambda b
\lambda\ge0
x,y\in K
0\le\lambda\le1
 A(\lambda x+(1-\lambda)y) =\lambda Ax + (1-\lambda)Ay\le \lambda b+(1-\lambda)b=b 
x\le x'
y\le y'
x+y\le x'+y'
